s that are highly likely to suffer from glaucoma are listed below:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>People aged over 40 years</li>\r\n 	<li>People with a family history of glaucoma</li>\r\n 	<li>East Asians, because of their shallower anterior chamber depth, as opposed to Caucasians</li>\r\n 	<li>People suffering from diabetes</li>\r\n 	<li>Some eye injuries, especially severe ones</li>\r\n 	<li>People with myopia (near-sightedness)</li>\r\n 	<li>Patients on long-term corticosteroids and metabolic disorders are highly likely to develop several different conditions, which include glaucoma. The risk is even higher in case of patients who regularly use eye drops that contain corticosteroids</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>'),(2219,368,'_page_content','field_5cee199f0b963'),(2220,93,'page_content','<div class=\"common-wrapper clear-both\">\r\n	<div class=\"row\">\r\n		<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n			<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-title\">Paediatric Ophthalmology and Squint Department <span class=\"float-right\">+</span></div>\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-desc\">\r\n\r\n<p>The paediatric ophthalmology services offered at H. V. Desai Eye Hospital are dedicated to provide comprehensive ophthalmic care to children aged below 16 years. The provision of these services is aimed at ensuring that no child is becomes blind, and to provide equal rights to children suffering from low vision as well as increased accessibility to all the possible medical services to enable them to play an active role in society. The paediatric ophthalmology services offered at the hospital provide treatment for all types vision-related problems in children, some of which are listed below:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Refractive error</li>\r\n 	<li>Amblyopia (Lazy eye)</li>\r\n 	<li>Paediatric cataract</li>\r\n 	<li>Paediatric squint</li>\r\n 	<li>Nystagmus</li>\r\n 	<li>Low vision</li>\r\n 	<li>Ocular trauma</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\nIn addition to the above-mentioned issues, the paediatric ophthalmology department, in collaboration with the retina department, takes an active part in screening and visually rehabilitating kids suffering from Retinopathy of Prematurity (ROP).\r\n</p><p>\r\nWith the glaucoma and oculoplasty department, common childhood problems such as paediatric glaucoma and oculoplasty disorders (nasolacrimal duct obstruction, ptosis, entropion, blepharophimosis, etc.) are also treated here. In addition, the strabismology services offered by this department provide treatment to adult patients suffering from double vision and squint.\r\n</p><p>\r\nThis department examines and treats around 10,000 patients each year, which include the surgical treatment of around 2,500 children per year.\r\n</p><p>\r\nThis department is also actively involved in school screening in the Pune and Satara districts to help in the earliest possible detection of ophthalmic conditions among children. This community outreach program helps paediatric patients to receive the best possible ophthalmic care at the earliest.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"accordion\">\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-title\">Education and Training\r\n\r\n<span class=\"float-right\">+</span></div>\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-desc\">\r\n<p>This department also has a structured fellowship program in paediatric ophthalmology and strabismus, which are listed below:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Short-term fellowship (3 months)</li>\r\n 	<li>Long-term fellowship(ORBIS supported) (15 months)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>'),(2221,93,'_page_content','field_5cee199f0b963'),(2222,369,'home_image',''),(2223,369,'_home_image','field_5cd00574bd707'),(2224,369,'page_content','<strong>Education and Training:</strong>\r\n\r\nThis department also has a structured fellowship program in paediatric ophthalmology and strabismus, which are listed below:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Short-term fellowship (3 months)</li>\r\n 	<li>Long-term fellowship(ORBIS supported) (15 months)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition to India, fellows from countries such as Nigeria and Kenya are also trained in this facility.\r\n\r\n<strong>Faculty:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Dr. Nikhil Rishikeshi</strong>\r\n\r\nHe is the Head of Department of Paediatric Ophthalmology and Strabismus, and is dedicated to providing comprehensive eye care for children. He has completed a long-term fellowship in paediatric ophthalmology, and has received training at the prestigious R.P. Centre for Ophthalmic Sciences (A.I.I.M.S.). As a paediatric surgeon, he is proficient in the treatment of cataracts and squint, and has a special interest in special forms of strabismus and nystagmus surgeries.\r\n\r\n<strong>Dr. Anushree Kaduskar-Aney</strong>\r\n\r\nShe has completed her DNB and long-term fellowship in paediatric ophthalmology from Sankara Nethralaya Chennai, and is a consultant in this department.\r\n\r\n<strong>Dr. Sudhir Taras</strong>\r\n\r\nHe is a formally trained paediatric orthoptist, and has received training at the Aravind Eye Hospital, Madurai. He is a devoted member of the team, and is highly dedicated to the treatment of eye problems in children, especially strabismus.'),(2225,369,'_page_content','field_5cee199f0b963'),(2226,370,'home_image',''),(2227,370,'_home_image','field_5cd00574bd707'),(2228,370,'page_content','<strong>Education and Training:</strong>\r\n\r\nThis department also has a structured fellowship program in paediatric ophthalmology and strabismus, which are listed below:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Short-term fellowship (3 months)</li>\r\n 	<li>Long-term fellowship(ORBIS supported) (15 months)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition to India, fellows from countries such as Nigeria and Kenya are also trained in this facility.\r\n<h4><strong>Faculty:</strong></h4>\r\n<strong>Dr. Nikhil Rishikeshi</strong>\r\n\r\nHe is the Head of Department of Paediatric Ophthalmology and Strabismus, and is dedicated to providing comprehe