values','field_5cdd3fe2ae149'),(3736,851,'page_description',''),(3737,851,'_page_description','field_5cdd0e073df07'),(3738,851,'vision_mission_values','<div class=\"three-box-wrapper clear-both\">\r\n<div class=\"award-images vision-mission-values-div\">\r\n<div class=\"award-1\">\r\n<div class=\"award-img\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/hvd/assets/images/vision.png\" alt=\"image-award\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"award-name\">\r\n<p><strong>Vision</strong></p>\r\nTo raise the standard of education, bring about overall development of the students, encourage them to undertake research in their respective fields and train students in comprehensive eye care that will bring about holistic development of the community.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"award-1\">\r\n<div class=\"award-img\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/hvd/assets/images/mission.png\" alt=\"image-award\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"award-name\">\r\n<p><strong>Mission</strong></p>\r\nWe are committed to provide comprehensive high quality, high volume eye care with affordable cost at the best satisfaction of patients and continually improve the eye care service.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"award-1\">\r\n<div class=\"award-img\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/hvd/assets/images/core-values.png\" alt=\"image-award\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"award-name\">\r\n<p><strong>Core Values</strong></p>\r\nTo facilitate the development of primary eye and Eye care and improve the availability and accessibility of high quality comprehensive vision services for all.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"common-wrapper clear-both\">\r\n	<div class=\"row\">\r\n		<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n			<div class=\"accordion active\">\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-title\">About the Course<span class=\"float-right\">+</span></div>\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-desc\">The admissions to BSc. Optom. Courses shall be carried out on the basis of the merit as ascertained from Science & Ophthal. Tech & Assist. Diploma Ophthalmic, HSC, PUC Board performance of the candidates in conducted by the University and their respective preference(s) given in application form.\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>20 Students will be admitted per year in the first year B. S c Optometry.</li>\r\n						<li>20 Students will be admitted per year in the first year Diploma in Optometry.</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n\r\n					<strong>Eligibility</strong>\r\n\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>Only the candidates who have passed 12th science with minimum 50% marks in each science subject will be considered.</li>\r\n						<li>A candidate who has passed course equivalent to 12th (10+2) like Ophthalmic Technician, Ophthalmic Assistant will be considered on a case by case basis. He should have secured 50% marks in the course.</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n					<strong>Admission Process</strong>\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>Forms will be available in the H. V. Desai Eye Hospital from 1st week of May. Completed forms should be submitted within the stipulated date. There will be an entrance examination of 50 marks.</li>\r\n						<li>Students will be called for interview according to the merit list. The admission will be confirmed only after full fees for the first academic year is paid & submission of original certificates.</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n					<strong>Duration of Course</strong>\r\n					The course will start in July every year and will consist for eight semesters including the practical training. First, Third and Fifth semester will start 1st July and end on 31st December and second semester will start from 1 St January and end on 30th June. Internship one year during that period practice exposure in General, Peadiatric, and subspecialty department. \r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"accordion\">\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-title\">Objectives of the Course<span class=\"float-right\">+</span></div>\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-desc\">\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>To prepare the students to assist the ophthalmologist in eye institutes, hospitals & primary eye care unit.</li>\r\n						<li>To enable students to estimate refractive errors and dispense glasses.</li>\r\n						<li>To enable students to use common instruments in the (just patients units and perform simple ophthalmic supervision)</li>\r\n						<li>To enable students to participate in eye health promotion activities in the community.</li>\r\n						<li>To enable the learners to teach optometry at a school/college of optometry, enable learners to conduct research in ophthalmic field.</li>\r\n						<li>To enable students to produce and select appropriate optical aids including spectacles and Low Vision devices.</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n					\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"accordion\">\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-title\">Scope and Career Options <span class=\"float-right\">+</span></div>\r\n				<div class=\"accordion-desc\">\r\n\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>Assist ophthalmologists in hospital / clinic.</li>\r\n						<li>Practice in optical establishments</li>\r\n						<li>Run optical shop</li>\r\n						<li>Have excellent job opportunities overseas.</li>\r\n						<li>Offer clinical services to multinationals dealing, with the manufacturing and distribution of ophthalmic lenses, contact lenses and ophthalmic instruments.</li>\r\n						<li>Start manufacturing unit for optical lenses.</li>\r\n						<li>For those interested in higher studies Graduation / Post Graduation in the form of fellowships, M.Sc., M. Phil and PhD programs are available.</li>\r\n						<li>Take up teaching Optometry as a career.</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n					<strong>Faculty</strong>(needs to be a separate heading. Layout same as doctors page)\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>Dr. Kalyani V. K. S</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. K. M .Bharucha</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Rahul Deshpande</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Sheetal Dharmadhikari</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Sucheta Kulkarni</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Kuldeep Dole</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Nana Jare</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Nilesh Kakade</li>\r\n						<li>Dr. Sudhir Ta