>Businessman</td></tr><tr><td>TRUSTEE</td><td>MR. DHANRAJ PATIL</td><td>SR NO 27/3, B, MUJABA VASTI NEAR GANESH TEMPLE, DHANORI,&nbsp;<br>PUNE - 411015</td><td>Social Worker</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->','Board Members/Trustees','','inherit','closed','closed','','273-revision-v1','','','2019-05-22 09:58:42','2019-05-22 09:58:42','',273,'http://test.hvd.com/2019/05/22/273-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(275,1,'2019-05-22 10:03:32','2019-05-22 10:03:32','<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"clear-both\"} -->\n<p class=\"clear-both\"><a href=\"/\">Home</a> / About Us / <strong> Accolades and Awards </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"award-pg clear-both\">\n    <div class=\"award-wrap\">\n        <div class=\"award-pg-img\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/hvd/assets/images/NABH.jpg\" class=\"mr-2 mb-2 float-left\">\n            <div class=\"award-pg-content\">\n               <p> <strong>NABH</strong> Accredited Hospital</p>\n<p>NABH (National Accreditation Board for Hospitals &amp; Healthcare Providers) is a constituent board of Quality Council of India, set up to establish and operate accreditation programme for healthcare organizations. Formed in 2005, it is the principal accreditation for hospitals in India.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"award-pg clear-both mt-5\">\n    <div class=\"award-wrap\">\n        <div class=\"award-pg-img\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/hvd/assets/images/Padma-Shri-Medallion.jpg\" class=\"mr-2 mb-2 float-left\">\n            <div class=\"award-pg-content\"><strong>Shri. N. P. Pandya</strong>&nbsp;has been awarded the most prestigious National Padma Award \"PADMASHRI\" for his dedicated and committed exemplary social work for 46 years in rehabilitation and prevention of blindness.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"award-pg clear-both mt-5\">\n    <div class=\"award-wrap\">\n        <div class=\"award-pg-img\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/hvd/assets/images/APAO.jpg\" class=\"mr-2 mb-2 float-left\">\n            <div class=\"award-pg-content\">\n                <p><strong>Dr. Col.(Retd) Madan Deshpande,</strong>&nbsp;Chief Medical Director, PBMA’s H. V. Desai Eye Hospital has been awarded \"Outstanding Service in Prevention of Blindness Award by Asia Pacific Academy of Ophthalmology(APAO) on 15th April 2012 in recognition of individuals that has made scientific contribution to prevention of blindness in the Asia Pacific Region. This APAO is the largest ophthalmic organization in their annual meeting at Busan, Korea where 65 countries have participated. This special award was conferred on Dr. Col. M. Deshpande. He is also presently President of VISION 2020: The Right to Sight–India, President of Indian Association of Community Ophthalmology (INACO ) and Community Ophthalmology Society of India (COSI). He is most popular and senior teacher, ophthalmologist and presently working to reduce the burden of avoidable blindness at the national level.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><br>\n\n</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','Accolades and Awards','','publish','closed','closed','','accolades-and-awards','','','2019-07-04 06:02:42','2019-07-04 06:02:42','',0,'http://test.hvd.com/?page_id=275',0,'page','',0),(276,1,'2019-05-22 10:03:32','2019-05-22 10:03:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Shri. N. P. Pandya</strong> has been awarded the most prestigious National Padma Award \"PADMASHRI\" for his dedicated and committed exemplary social work for 46 years in rehabilitation and prevention of blindness.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Dr. Col.(Retd) Madan Deshpande,</strong>&nbsp;Chief Medical Director, PBMA’s H. V. Desai Eye Hospital has been awarded \"Outstanding Service in Prevention of Blindness Award by Asia Pacific Academy of Ophthalmology(APAO) on 15th April 2012 in recognition of individuals that has made scientific contribution to prevention of blindness in the Asia Pacific Region. This APAO is the largest ophthalmic organization in their annual meeting at Busan, Korea where 65 countries have participated. This special award was conferred on Dr. Col. M. Deshpande. He is also presently President of VISION 2020: The Right to Sight–India, President of Indian Association of Community Ophthalmology (INACO ) and Community Ophthalmology Society of India (COSI). He is most popular and senior teacher, ophthalmologist and presently working to reduce the burden of avoidable blindness at the national level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><br>\n\n</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','Accolades and Awards','','inherit','closed','closed','','275-revision-v1','','','2019-05-22 10:03:32','2019-05-22 10:03:32','',275,'http://test.hvd.com/2019/05/22/275-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(277,1,'2019-05-22 10:13:37','2019-05-22 10:13:37','<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"breadcrumbs mb-4\"><span> About Us </span>/<span><strong> Success Stories</strong></span></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nA quick glance at few opportunities received by the hospital&nbsp;<br>to restore the vision of the needy.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Success Stories','','publish','closed','closed','','success-stories','','','2019-06-27 09:57:24','2019-06-27 09:57:24','',0,'http://test.hvd.com/?page_id=277',0,'page','',0),(278,1,'2019-05-22 10:13:37','2019-05-22 10:13:37','','Success stories','','inherit','closed','closed','','277-revision-v1','','','2019-05-22 10:13:37','2019-05-22 10:13:37','',277,'http://test.hvd.com/2019/05/22/277-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(279,1,'2019-05-22 10:16:11','2019-05-22 10:16:11','<!-- wp:html -->\n<p><a href=\"/\">Home</a> / About Us / <strong> Our Supporters </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!--