-06-13 09:41:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"/\">Home</a> / About Us / <strong> Accolades and Awards </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Shri. N. P. Pandya</strong>&nbsp;has been awarded the most prestigious National Padma Award \"PADMASHRI\" for his dedicated and committed exemplary social work for 46 years in rehabilitation and prevention of blindness.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Dr. Col.(Retd) Madan Deshpande,</strong>&nbsp;Chief Medical Director, PBMA’s H. V. Desai Eye Hospital has been awarded \"Outstanding Service in Prevention of Blindness Award by Asia Pacific Academy of Ophthalmology(APAO) on 15th April 2012 in recognition of individuals that has made scientific contribution to prevention of blindness in the Asia Pacific Region. This APAO is the largest ophthalmic organization in their annual meeting at Busan, Korea where 65 countries have participated. This special award was conferred on Dr. Col. M. Deshpande. He is also presently President of VISION 2020: The Right to Sight–India, President of Indian Association of Community Ophthalmology (INACO ) and Community Ophthalmology Society of India (COSI). He is most popular and senior teacher, ophthalmologist and presently working to reduce the burden of avoidable blindness at the national level.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><br>\n\n</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','Accolades and Awards','','inherit','closed','closed','','275-revision-v1','','','2019-06-13 09:41:34','2019-06-13 09:41:34','',275,'http://test.hvd.com/2019/06/13/275-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(446,1,'2019-06-13 09:43:20','2019-06-13 09:43:20','<!-- wp:html -->\n<p><a href=\"/\">Home</a> / About Us / <strong> Our Supporters </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Rotary International</li><li>CBM , Germany</li><li>NPCB- National Prevention and Control of Blindness, Government of India (District Bli